"{\"abstract\":\"Identifying people in historical photographs is important for interpreting material culture, correcting the historical record,and creating economic value, but it is also a complex and challenging task. In this paper, we focus on identifying portraits of soldiers who participated in the American Civil War (1861\\u201365). Millions of these portraits survive, but only 10\\u201320% are identified. We created Photo Sleuth, a web-based platform that combines crowdsourced human expertise and automated face recognition to support Civil War portrait identification. Our mixed-methods evaluation of Photo Sleuth one month after its public launch showed that it helped users successfully identify unknown portraits.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"32698591\",\"name\":\"V. Mohanty\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/32698591\"},{\"authorId\":\"51219402\",\"name\":\"David Thames\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/51219402\"},{\"authorId\":\"20402239\",\"name\":\"Sneha Mehta\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/20402239\"},{\"authorId\":\"144647604\",\"name\":\"Kurt Luther\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144647604\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":220484641,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2020/660\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":false,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"19fb88cca7d2f8c4491e4444727549d66b8fed60\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Jacey Fortin\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"\",\"title\":\"A Photo of Billy the Kid Bought for $10 at a Flea Market May Be Worth Millions\",\"url\":\"\",\"venue\":\"The New York Times, January\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"144694958\",\"name\":\"T. Erickson\"},{\"authorId\":\"1710155\",\"name\":\"W. Kellogg\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1145/34494